f the scientists who created devastating weapons, exploring the espionage of the nuclear arms race, and exposing the role of human error in nuclear disaster, The Manhattan Project is a necropastoral exploration of the literal and figurative fallout of the nuclear age. These poems wail like a meltdown siren, condemning anthropocentric thinking for its self-destructive arrogance.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAtomic bomb-History. 0aManhattan Project (U.S.)-History. 0aNuclear energyvPoetry. 0aNuclear weaponsvPoetry. 7aPOETRY / Canadian.2bisacsh  aAtomic Bomb Literature.  aAtomic Bomb.  aAtomic Spies.  aAtomic War.  aBooks About Nuclear War.  aCold War.  aJoyelle McSweeney.  aKen Hunt Poet.  aKen Hunt Poetry.  aNecropastoral Poetry.  aNecropastoral.  aNuclear Apocalypse.  aNuclear Disaster, Nuclear Medicine.  aNuclear Espionage.  aNuclear Literature.  aNuclear Poems.  aNuclear Poetry.  aNuclear Secrets.  aNuclear War Poems.  aPoetry of the Nuclear Age.  aSpacecraft Press.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311127253508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020z978311127473740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773850559?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773850559423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773850559/original  a978-3-11-127253-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-127473-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles